  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ 400°F/ Gas 6 and boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Meanwhile, wash the <strong>leek</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium heat and once hot, add the <strong>sliced leeks</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until they've softened</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and chop the <strong>potatoes</strong> into rough, bite-<span class=\"text-highlight\">sized</span> pieces</p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> over a high heat and cook for 10-15 min or until fork-tender</p>\n<p>Once cooked, drain and return them to the pot</p>\n<p>Return the drained <strong>potatoes</strong> to a low heat and add a splash of <strong>milk</strong> and a large knob of <strong>butter </strong>and mash until smooth</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>chicken <span class=\"text-highlight\">thighs</span></strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Once the <strong>leeks</strong> have softened, add the <strong>chopped </strong><strong>chicken</strong> to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 3-4 min</p>\n<p>Strip the <strong>thyme</strong> <strong>leaves</strong> from their stalks and add them to the pan (don't worry if some of the stalks make it into the pan <span class=\"text-highlight\">too)</span></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add 15g <span class=\"text-danger\">[30g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> to the pan</p>\n<p>Once melted, add 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min</p>\n<p>Gradually stir in 200ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[400ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> and season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> <span class=\"text-highlight\">–</span> this is your <strong>chicken and leek mixture</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Pour the <strong>chicken and leek mixture</strong> into the base of an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> </p>\n<p>Spread the <strong>mash</strong> evenly on top and run a fork over the top to give it <span class=\"text-highlight\">an</span> extra <span class=\"text-highlight\">crunch</span></p>\n<p>Put the dish in the oven and cook for 15-20 min or until it's golden and bubbling</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, wipe the pan clean</p>\n<p>Top, tail, peel and chop the <strong>carrot</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"><strong>[s]</strong></span> into quarters lengthways</p>\n<p>Cut at an angle into small bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Boil a kettle</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/949.-step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Return the pan to a medium heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped </strong><strong>carrot</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until it's starting to brown</p>\n<p>Once the <strong>carrots</strong> are lightly browned, add the <strong>green beans</strong> with a knob of <strong>butter</strong>, a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 50ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>\n<p>Cook, covered, for 8-9 min or until the <strong>carrots</strong> are tender</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
